== Description == [[File:Thimble - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Thimble|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967683653674340606}}]] Thimble is four inches tall and looks to be about eighteen years old. She has short, brown hair and bright spring green wings. She has rosey pale skin and a few freckles on her face.<!-- Insert character description here. -->
=== Personality === <!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.--> {{clr|left}}
== Biography == As a fairy, Thimble is from [[Tír Cruthú]], also known as Faerie.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|2:26:10}} She was gifted to [[Thjazi Fang]] as a wedding present.{{ep ref|ep=4x2|1:01:56}} Thimble started aging when the doors to Faerie were closed.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|2:28:25}}
She fought alongside Thjazi as part of the [[Torn Banner]] for many years, and was known as Thjazi’s partner “in all things”.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|02:10:00}}
In the two weeks following Thjazi's arrest, Thimble, [[Thaisha Lloy]], [[Azune Nayar]], [[Casimir Gavendale]], [[Occtis Tachonis]], and [[Cyd Pridesire]] formulated a plan to rescue him, involving Thimble creating a glyph of Misty Step and planting it on Thjazi.
=== [[Campaign 4]] === The safehouse Thimble was staying in was attacked and robbed before she could deliver the glyph, and she took down three assailants before falling unconscious. She was found by [[Teor Pridesire]], Azune, and Occtis following Thjazi’s execution. They informed her of Thjazi’s death and together they tried to put together why she was attacked. [[Kattigan Vale]] joined them and determined the attackers had likely been [[Crow Keepers]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} She, along with the others, went to [[Hal]]'s house to Thjazi's wake, where she wept over his body and asked [[Vaelus]] if she'd been the attacker. Vaelus told her she had not been. She and the other Torn Banner members, as well as Occtis, looked at the glyph that had been on Thjazi when he died and found that it had been a clever fake, and they discussed that the two missing members from the plan were Casimir and Cyd. Thimble decided to pursue the lead on Casimir in the morning, and stayed at Hal's, sleeping on Thjazi's chest. The following morning, Kattigan returned, and he and Occtis joined her in going to the [[Guard Tower]] to find Casimir. Before leaving, Thimble gave Hal a letter to give to [[Bolaire]], and Hal told her she could always stay at his home if she needed a place. At the Guard Tower, when she asked about Casimir, she, Kattigan, and Occtis were immediately attacked.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} The fight went poorly until Vaelus, who had followed them, arrived and joined, killing two Crow Keepers. The rest fled except one they asked to stay and interrogate, who told them Casimir had been deeply in debt and had just paid it off in full the previous day, and had had a deed to a fortress in [[Gormalay]] as well, but that had been taken by Cyd. The group returned to Hal's, realizing Casimir had sold them out. There they encountered [[Julien]], who was looking for Occtis, but grabbed Thimble by the wings briefly in telling them this. Occtis and Vaelus left with him, and Kattigan and Thimble told Hal, Thaisha, Azune, and Murray what had happened when they returned. They also told Teor when he returned, bringing [[Wick]] and [[Tyranny]]. Thimble and Kattigan realized the Crow Keepers would likely give them trouble, and Teor, Wick, and Tyranny had to flee [[House Halovar]], so they all decided to leave the city and pursue Casimir and Cyd.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}
