'''Azune Nayar''' ({{Audio|Azune Nayar pronunciation - 4x01.ogg|pronunciation}}) is a [[human]] [[paladin]]/[[sorcerer]] and Arcane Marshal of the [[Revolutionary Guard]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Luis Carazo]].

== Description ==
[[File:Azune Nayar - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Azune Nayar|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679672629727295}}]]

Azune appears human. He is over 5'10" tall and had medium brown skin, coppery auburn hair tied back into a braid, and a birthmark on the right side of his neck. His eyes are described as "a sunset on the ocean": sun-yellow pupils "that burst" into orange, teal, then light gray with irises that are deep blue on the bottom half. He is strong, lean, and muscular. His right bicep is tattooed with the words "Have mercy on those I send you".{{ep ref|ep=4x01|6:17}}

He wears the armor of the Revolutionary Guard with his arms exposed.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|6:17}}

=== Personality ===
[[Luis Carazo]] stated that Azune is interested in exploring the nature of the afterlife after the death of the [[Shapers]].{{ep ref|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=94mCyd_2Q_Y|ep=Critical Role Cast Interview with Brennan Lee Mulligan Campaign 4|6:49}} When describing Azune in one word, Luis chose "observant".{{ep ref|ep=CRITICAL ROLE CAMPAIGN 4 INTERVIEW! MULTIPLE TABLES! NO ONE TRUSTS MATT MERCER! Brennan Lee Mulligan|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vUHrc_fXzZo&t=1s|11:54}}
{{clr|left}}

== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
Azune was left by his father when he was a teenager. At 15 years old, he fought as a rebel in the [[Falconer's Rebellion]] as part of the [[Torn Banner]] under the command of [[Loza Blade]] alongside [[Thjazi Fang]], [[Thimble]], [[Kattigan Vale]], [[Teor Pridesire]], and [[Casimir Gavendale]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|1:58}} At some point, Azune joined the [[Revolutionary Guard]] in [[Dol-Makjar]] and became an Arcane Marshal.

In the two weeks following Thjazi's arrest, Azune, Thimble, Casimir, [[Thaisha Lloy]], [[Occtis Tachonis]], and [[Cyd Pridesire]] formulated a plan to rescue him, involving Thimble creating a glyph of ''Misty Step'' and planting it on Thjazi. Azune would be part of the proceedings to scan Thjazi for errant magic and falsely claim to find nothing.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|2h36m16s}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Azune checked Thjazi for magic as he was led to the gallows. Over ''Message'', Azune informed Thjazi that someone placed a glyph on him earlier, then relayed a message from Thjazi's brother [[Halandil Fang]]: Thjazi was always a hero in Hal's eyes. Assuring Thjazi that the work he started in the city continues, Azune cast ''Detect Magic'' to find what he believed was the glyph. He cleared Thjazi to be taken forward and indicated to him the glyph's location. However, Thjazi was still hanged and killed.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}}

Afterward, Azune brought Thjazi's body to Hal's home for the [[Farramh]], and he smoothed out Thjazi's features to hide his fear in his last moments. He watched Hal closely throughout the event to help him host the many guests. After an initial wariness, he and Teor reunited warmly, and Azune assured him that many in Dol-Makjar felt Thjazi's execution was an injustice. Growing concerned that Teor also had not seen Cyd, his brother, he, Occtis, and Teor went to Thjazi's safe house, where Thimble created the glyph. They found the place ransacked, Thimble severely injured, and the glyph still in her possession. Azune realized that something else was planted on Thjazi, and the group found that the [[Stone of Nightsong]] was stolen from the safe house, apparently by the [[Crow Keepers]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01}}

The group returned to Hal's house, where Azune discovered the item he detected on Thjazi was made to appear genuine using ''Magic Aura''. The following day, at work, Azune encountered [[Harondus Einfasen]] and learned that the [[Sundered Houses]] were taking over management of the [[Revolutionary Guard]], though not the Arcane Marshals such as himself. He then headed to Caravan Hill,{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} where [[Murray]] found him, and the two discussed the power grabs the Sundered Houses were taking in their respective workplaces. From there they went back to Hal's, having learned about a fracas at the [[Guard Tower]], and Azune was updated on Casimir's betrayal by Thimble. After Teor arrived with [[Wick]] and [[Tyranny]], Azune realized that group as well as Thimble and Kattigan, having fought the [[Crow Keepers]], needed to leave the city quickly, and most were also interested in tracking down Casimir. He helped them get horses and escape, and remained behind, reciting the names of the Falcon's Rest.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

