== Description == [[File:Julien Davinos - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Julien Davinos|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679657740013744}}]] Julien is a human man in his thirties, with a lanky build. He has long, curly black hair.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:17:09}} He wears the reinforced leather military uniform of House Davinos, with a short green cape featuring vine and flower embroidery. His left hand is covered by a large and ornate silver gauntlet.
=== Personality === <!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.--> {{clr|left}} == Biography == Julien is a member of [[House Davinos]], a vassal house to the [[Sundered House]] of [[House Royce]]. [[Aranessa Royce]] is an old childhood friend of his.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:16:45}}
He is considered the "hero of the Battle of Maharlian Falls" in the [[Falconer's Rebellion]] for knocking [[Thjazi Fang]] off his horse and bringing him to justice.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:20:22}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === After the execution of Thjazi Fang, Sir Julian accompanied Lady Aranessa to Thjazi's wake in [[Halandil Fang]]'s home. When he approached the threshold, [[Thaisha]] let the plants she had ''Druidcrafted'' wither around him. She then met him outside and the two had a heated discussion about his attitude and his tutelage of Thaisha's son [[Alogar]], but were interrupted by the arrival of [[Vaelus]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} He and Aranessa left sometime later, and she told him [[Raimond Davinos|his father]] was waiting to see him the next day, at which he looked angry. He instead went to a brothel, and was woken up by his father tracking him down and yelling his name the following morning. He dressed and left with his father, who berated him for his behavior, indicating this was a pattern, as they rode to the [[Palazzo Davinos]]. There, Raimond and Aranessa spoke about their supply caravans having been stopped on the far side of the [[Dvalmar Pass]] and expressed concern about [[House Tachonis]]. They tasked Julien to find [[Occtis]], who the Tachonis family was searching for on suspected connection to a plan to free Thjazi, and Julien left to do so after his father threw water in his face to sober him up.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} On his way, he encountered [[Teor Pridesire]] in the marketplace and realized he was likely being sent to be killed by the [[House Halovar]] fixers, but did not tell him this and continued on to Hal's to find Occtis. When [[Thimble]], [[Kattigan]], Occtis, and Vaelus returned to the house, Occtis in disguise, he grabbed Thimble by the wings and dismissed her value and let her go before telling the group that Occtis was in danger. Occtis believed him and decided to follow him, and Vaelus joined him. He brought them to the Palazzo Davinos, where his father and Aranessa received the guests. He then, instead of drinking with several friends, went to speak to Vaelus, who was in the garden, about how he felt uneasy about what was happening. Their conversation was interrupted when members of house Tachonis assassinated Raimond.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}
