'''Tyranny''' is a [[demon]] warlock and Aspirant of the [[Candescent Creed]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], she is played by [[Whitney Moore]].

== Description ==
[[File:Tyranny - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Tyranny|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679648306995452}}]]
<!-- Insert character description here. -->

===Appearance===
Tyranny is a demon with bubblegum pink skin and straight white hair in blunt bangs, partially slipping out of a wimple. She has yellow goat eyes, goat hooves and ears that are extremely soft,{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:55:56}} of which the right one is pierced with an arrow-shaped silver earring. Tyranny has a distinctive scent resembling chocolate chip laced with sulfur.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:21:00}}

=== Personality ===
Whitney describes Tyranny as "fresh to the world" of Aramán, as someone from a different [[plane]], and looking to enjoy herself.{{ep ref|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=94mCyd_2Q_Y|ep=Critical Role Cast Interview with Brennan Lee Mulligan Campaign 4|4:22}} She also is described as more tender than she initially appears.{{ep ref|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XMCeXvy580s|ep=Critical Role Campaign 4 Cast Interview - Brennan Lee Mulligan as DM, campaign themes and more!|7:03}}
{{clr|left}}
== Biography ==
=== Prior to Campaign 4 ===
Tyranny was given corporeal form six months prior to [[Thjazi Fang]]'s execution, having previously been a soul in the [[Pit]]. She was assigned to [[Wicander Halovar]] as an Aspirant. Unlike him, she knew that the [[Candescent Creed]] was false, but she found that Wick seemed to be a better person than the others of his family and grew fond of him.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|42:20}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Tyranny and Wick watched the execution, and Tyranny's sister [[Enmity]] berated her for her "dimmings". They later arrived at Thjazi's farramh following his execution and were given a somewhat chilly reception, as [[House Halovar]] had had a hand in the execution. She drank an entire bottle of liquor and went to the kitchen with [[Olgud Akarat|Olgud]] to get more for Wick, until [[Thaisha]] found her and intervened. The two hit it off, and Thaisha got drunk and confided in Tyranny about her past. When [[Bolaire]] arrived, he made small talk with Tyranny, who had vomited in an artifact at the Archanade some months ago. After [[Aranessa]] arrived, and began asking Wick why she had not been given an audience with [[Yanessa Halovar|his grandmother]], Tyranny vomited again and used it as an excuse to leave and take Wick with her.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} The following day, she went to answer the door for [[Teor]]'s appointment with Wick, and as she did, her sisters Enmity, [[Cruelty]], and [[Agony (character)|Agony]] all spoke to her in the hall, indicating they knew Wick was ignorant of the true nature of the Creed. She then let Teor in and fetched Wick, who was somewhat nervous. The two saw Teor heal an injured worker. They spoke with him until Yanessa joined them and sent Teor to [[Filoneus]]. Later that night, Tyranny joined Wick as he was brought downstairs to learn the truth about the Halovar's power and was shown [[Aetheon]], the [[celestial]] they had imprisoned who was the true source of [[Filament]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} Following this revelation Tyranny suggested she draw Wick a bath, and Yanessa agreed that would be thoughtful. Once there, she told Wick that she hadn't wanted to lie to him, but had to, and that his family had a deal with hers, but her contract was to him and he could dismiss her if he wanted. She also told him she suspected Teor had been sent to his death, and encouraged him to help her rescue him. Wick agreed, and the two went to the [[Mercanaud Couturier]], where Tyranny was able to convince [[Rulius and Calastro Mercanaud]] to release Teor to them. They all went to [[Hal]]'s house, where Teor learned his brother [[Cyd]] had fled chasing [[Casimir]], who had betrayed the plan to save Thjazi. Teor told Tyranny and Wick he owed them for saving his life, and they, along with Thimble and Kattigan, all realized they should flee the city and follow Casimir's trail.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

