'''Halandil''' "'''Hal'''" '''Fang''' is an [[orc]] [[bard]], the brother of [[Thjazi Fang]], and the owner of the [[Hallowed Round]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Liam O'Brien]].

== Description ==
[[File:Halandil Fang - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Halandil Fang|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679670117355613}}]]
Halandil is an older orc with dark hair with streaks of white and smile lines at the eyes from a life well lived. He dresses in fine but not ostentatious clothing. {{ep ref|ep=4x01|0:14}}
=== Personality ===
<!-- Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.-->

{{clr|left}}
== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
Halandil fought in part of the [[War of Axe and Vine]].{{ep ref|ep=4x1|1:05:17}} He and Thaisha were romantically involved and had [[Alogar]] and [[Shadia]], their children, together, when they were younger, and after Thaisha left to adventure, he raised the children. He and Thaisha are still close.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|40:40}} After Thjazi was captured, Hal had tried to stay the execution peacefully through political channels with [[Wicander Halovar]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:49:40}} He also, earlier the day of Thjazi's execution, received the deed to the [[Dithyramb of Azgra]], an amphitheater he had long wanted.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:48:09}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
[[Azune]] helped Hal be able to speak with Thjazi shortly before his execution, and when Thjazi realized he was indeed about to die he frantically told him to help [[Murray]], that [[Bolaire]] has paint, and to tell [[Thimble]] not to be afraid. Hal then hosted the wake for Thjazi, sharing moments with his family and friends. When Wick arrived, the two went upstairs and Hal asked him what had happened, regarding [[House Halovar]]'s choice to go through with the execution. Wick told him he did not know, but gave Hal Thjazi's sword.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} After [[Vaelus]] arrived, Thaisha opened the box she had brought for Thjazi from [[Venatus]], and fell unconscious, at which Hal healed her. Later, after most of the guests left, he and his daughter Hero, from his other partner [[Elodie]], played "Broken Wing", an anthem of the [[Falconer's Rebellion]] for the remaining guests. He asked Vaelus to leave as everyone went to bed, as they did not have the [[Stone of Nightsong]] she was searching for, and she did; Thaisha, [[Occtis Tachonis|Occtis]], and Thimble slept at the house. The following morning, he told Thimble she was always welcome at his home, and made breakfast with Thaisha.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}}

Later that day, Hal visited the theater, renamed the [[Hallowed Round]], with Thaisha and various members of his troupe. Bolaire came by with the paints, and Hal asked about them as he had only heard of them shortly before Thjazi died. He later returned home to find Thimble and [[Kattigan]], who had discovered that [[Casimir Gavendale]] had betrayed Thjazi and likely been the person who attacked Thimble. Hal, realizing [[Teor]] had not returned, sent out messengers, but Teor soon after arrived with Wick and [[Tyranny]], having been rescued by them from the [[Mercanaud Couturier]]. After some discussion, Kattigan, Thimble, Teor, Tyranny, and Wick realized they needed to leave the city for their own safety and could use the opportunity to track Casimir. As they left, Hal pulled aside Thimble and told her to find Casimir, Inspiring her.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

