'''Wicander "Wick" Halovar''' is an [[aasimar]] sorcerer of the [[Candescent Creed]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Sam Riegel]].

== Description ==
[[File:Wicander Halovar - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Wicander Halovar|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679675028869126}}]]
Wicander is a tall{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:19:28|more=Sam describes Wicander as "a tall man, 5'11"}} and beautiful human man, with light teal and white hair. He has pearlescent face markings over half of his face, that seem to shimmer with a light of their own. He wears light teal robes. He carries a cane with the symbol of the Candescent Creed.

=== Personality ===
Wicander is greatly preoccupied with his role as a scion of [[House Halovar]] and a Light Priest of the Candescent Creed. He often quotes the texts of the Creed, and attempts to follow its tenets in his daily life.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:46:52}}

{{clr|left}}

== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
At some point, Wick fell in love with a commoner but was not permitted to marry her.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|0:49:07}}

In the few weeks leading up to [[Thjazi Fang]]'s execution, [[Halandil Fang]] worked with Wick to attempt to have his family stay the execution.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:53:21}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
At the execution, Wick was told by [[Yanessa Halovar|his grandmother]] moments before it occurred that House Halovar would be calling for it along with [[House Tachonis]], which was a shock to him. Later, he and [[Tyranny]] arrived at Thjazi's wake at Hal's home, Wick bringing Thjazi's sword to give to Hal. After Tyranny gave him a drink, Wick was called to Hal's study. Hal asked him what had happened, and Wick told him he'd tried, but Hal was hesitant to trust him. He then rejoined the wake, and [[Loza Blade]] recognized the sword. When she did, Wick gave it to Hal. She also set up a meeting between Wick and her companion [[Teor Pridesire]] for an interview as a guard. Lady [[Aranessa]] arrived soon after and was, unbeknownst to him, extremely angry with Wick and the Candescent Creed. After she began to ask Wick why she'd been denied an audience with his house, Tyranny pretended to vomit and the two left quickly.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}}

The following day, Wick met with Teor and was interrupted by Yanessa, who sent Teor to be outfitted and told Wick to get rid of him. When Wick seemed confused as to why, she grew openly frustrated with him and told him to be less naive, that their house was once priests in [[Obridimia]], and that they needed to maintain good terms with House Tachonis for the sake of their own power. She told him she would reveal more that night. Wick's father, Lord [[Godard]], called on him that night and brought him and Tyranny deep below the [[Villa Aurora]] into a basement, and along with Yanessa, revealed that they had a massive [[celestial]] named [[Aetheon]] kept captive, and that [[Filament]] was the product of Aetheon, his grandfather.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} Yanessa then explained further that she had used Filament to cast a spell and had given birth to Godard as a result. She also explained the truth: following the death of the [[Shapers]], she had developed the Candescent Creed as people still needed religion, and as a source of wealth and power for the family. Wick's mother [[Iris Halovar|Iris]] loved the Creed and requested Wick be raised as a true believer and as the face of the family so he could make an advantageous political marriage; everyone else, including his sister [[Zebani Halovar|Zebani]] and the [[demon]]s were aware the Creed had been created by Yanessa and Filament came from Aetheon. Wick was taken aback but said he would continue as the scion of the house, and Tyranny suggested he take a bath. Upstairs in his chambers, Tyranny explained that not only was everything Yanessa had said true, but that the Halovars had a deal with her family for power, that they were afraid of his willpower and moral certainty and that was why they'd told him the truth, and that Teor was likely on his way to be killed. The two of them decided to leave together to rescue Teor. They did so, though Tyranny did most of the talking at the [[Mercanaud Couturier]], and then headed to Hal's house. There, they learned that Teor's brother had left the city yesterday in pursuit of [[Casimir Gavendale]], who had sold out Thjazi, and, upon realizing they were themselves about to be wanted by House Halovar, fled the city with [[Thimble]] and [[Kattigan]] to track Casimir to [[Gormalay]].{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}

