 a [[nama]] paladin and mercenary of the [[Torn Banner]]. As a player character in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Travis Willingham]].
== Description == [[File:Teor Pridesire - Solelle.jpg|300px|thumb|left|{{caption|subject=Teor Pridesire|artist=Solelle|artist2=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://x.com/CriticalRole/status/1967679646117532162}}]] Teor is a light tan and grey nama. He has yellow eyes. On the left side of his face he has a long scar starting at just above the eyebrow bone and going down to just under his lips. He has a long grey mane, some of which is braided with a purple band and worn over his shoulders. He has a beard which is also braided with a purple band.
=== Personality === Teor is described as stoic.{{ep ref|ep=The Cast of Critical Role Discusses Campaign 4|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=J9Mtkh1FUPA|1:08}} {{clr|left}}
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Teor served in the [[Torn Banner]] during the [[Falconer's Rebellion]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|5:47}} He remained with his commander [[Loza Blade]] as a mercenary afterwards, and they returned to [[Dol-Makjar]] shortly prior to [[Thjazi]]'s execution.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:05:54}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === Teor and Loza came to Thjazi's funeral together. There, Teor reunited with [[Azune]], who had also served with them, and told Azune he had hoped to settle back in town because his brother [[Cyd]] still lived here. He and Azune, along with [[Occtis]], left the funeral after a few hours to investigate Thjazi's safe house. There, they found it ransacked, and [[Thimble]] unconscious. Teor healed her, and the group broke the news of Thjazi's death to her. [[Kattigan]], who had also served in the Torn Banner, joined, having followed the others, and was able to determine a likely lead on who had attacked Thimble.{{ep ref|ep=4x01}} They returned to the wake and updated others involved in the plan to save Thjazi with what had happened. Teor learned that Cyd had been part of the plan from Azune and Occtis, and told them that Cyd was generally not very trustworthy and had a history of stealing. Upon leaving the wake with Loza, she told him that she would be retiring and heading further west, but gave him a case containing half of a banner that had once been the pennant of the now disbanded Torn Banner. She also told him she had set up a meeting with [[Wicander Halovar]] for a security job for him. The following day, he went to the meeting, and while waiting for Wick healed a worker who was injured when a crate fell. Wick seemed amenable to hiring him, as did [[Tyranny]], but [[Yanessa Halovar]] felt he was asking too many questions and sent him to [[Filoneus Halovar]]{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} to pass on to the [[Mercanaud Couturier]], the house's fixers. On the way, Teor encountered [[Julien]], who realized that Teor was likely being sent to his death, but did not intervene. At the Couterier, once [[Rulius and Calastro Mercanaud]] realized Teor had been sent to be "outfitted", they captured him and began cutting up his shadow. However, Tyranny and Wick, having decided to save Teor after Wick had learned the truth about the [[Candescent Creed]], convinced the Mercanaud twins to let Teor go. They all went to [[Hal]]'s home, where they met Thimble and Kattigan, who told them [[Casimir Gavendale]], another former member of the Torn Banner, was the traitor, and Cyd had run after him in pursuit towards [[Gormalay]]. They all realized they needed to leave the city as they were in danger from [[House Halovar]] or the [[Crow Keepers]] and with Azune's help left that night.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}
