{{Infobox Character | image = File:Thjazi Fang portrait - Hannah Friederichs.jpg | caption = {{caption|subject=Thjazi Fang|artist=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hdLPwuKMlIY}} <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = Araman | actor = Brennan Lee Mulligan | class = | species = [[Orc]] <!-- Biographical information --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = | AKA = Thaz{{ep ref|ep=4x02|55:47}} | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | place = [[Dol-Makjar]], [[Aramán]] | family = {{tree list}} * [[Fang family]] ** [[Halandil Fang]] (brother) {{tree list/end}} | partner = [[Aranessa Royce]] (wife) | children = | profession = | affiliations = [[Torn Banner]] <!-- Status --> | status = Deceased | deathReason = Hanged by the [[Sundered Houses]] — {{ep|4x01}} <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Delete this section if the character is unlikely to ever get stats --> | statsArray1 = {{Infobox Character/stats| | system = d&d | creatureType = Humanoid | background = <!-- Mechanical background, i.e. "Haunted One" --> | alignment = | level = | HP = | AC = | DC = | str = | dex = | con = | int = | wis = | cha = | statsRef = }} <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x01}} | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (1 episode) }} '''Thjazi Fang''' is an [[orc]] in [[Aramán]]. Described as a "hero to many [and] enemy to some", his sudden and impending execution is the precipitating event of [[Campaign 4]]. As a [[non-player character]], he is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Thjazi is an [[orc]] with dark, graying hair.{{ep ref|intro=Thumbnail for|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jgK_qRwpygA|ep=Critical Role IV {{!}} Official Trailer}}
=== Personality ===
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Thjazi grew up with his mother and his and [[Halandil Fang]]'s father on the edge of the Rookery in [[Dol-Makjar]].{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:56:07}}
He fought in the [[War of Axe and Vine]]. He married [[Aranessa Royce]], a noblewoman of the [[Sundered Houses]]. As a wedding present, he was gifted the [[fairy]] [[Thimble]], and the two became best friends.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|1:01:56}} Two years later, he participated in the [[Falconer's Rebellion]], and Aranessa's grandfather sided against Thjazi.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:23:25}} Thjazi is described as having lived a "remarkable life" and became a "hero to many [and] enemy to some". He felt that he "didn't get in nearly as much trouble as I wanted to".<ref name="Trailer"/>
At the end of the [[Falconer's Rebellion]],{{ep ref|ep=4x02|3:07:36}} he was knocked off his horse and brought to the authorities by [[Julien Davinos]]. He was granted clemency.{{ep ref|ep=4x1|3:24:27}}
Several years prior to his death, Thjazi learned the truth about [[Bolaire]]'s nature, and used this to blackmail Bolaire into providing him with artifacts from the museum. He also forbid Bolaire from telling this to Hal, whom Bolaire had befriended. Thimble served as go-between in this arrangement.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|3:52:44}} In the months leading up to his death, Thjazi had also sent [[Thaisha]] and [[Occtis]] to retrieve an item from [[Venatus]], which turned out to be a coffin of [[Olbalad]], the psychopomp [[celestial]] of [[Rauwyn]];{{ep ref|ep=4x02|21:30}} and had himself stolen the [[Stone of Nightsong]] from the [[Sisters of Sylandri]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|1:26:35}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === [[File:Thjazi Fang - Hannah Friederichs.png|thumb|left|200px|{{caption|nointro=true|subject=Thjazi Fang|artist=Hannah Friederichs|source=https://critrole.com/campaign4/}}]] Thjazi was suddenly jailed and sentenced to death in the city of [[Dol-Makjar]], drawing people from throughout his life together to find the truth behind his impending execution.<ref>{{CR|what-is-campaign-4|What Is Campaign Four?}}</ref> As his execution approached, he described himself as "beset by enemies on all sides".{{ep ref|vod=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jgK_qRwpygA|ep=Critical Role IV {{!}} Official Trailer|name="Trailer"}} Despite efforts from his brother Hal to make a deal with [[House Halovar]] to stay his execution,{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:50:49}} and a plan in which Thimble would create a rune to transport Thjazi away from the gallows, which [[Azune]] would not report when doing his scan as an [[Arcane Marshal]], after which [[Cyd Pridesire]] would serve as the driver of a getaway car that Occtis and Thaisha would meet,{{ep ref|ep=4x01|2:36:16}} both plans failed and Thjazi was executed.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|18:34}} Prior to his death, with the help of Azune's ''Message'' spell, he was able to speak with Hal. He grew panicky upon seeing something in the sky and told Hal that [[Bolaire]] had paints, to help [[Murray]], and to tell [[Thimble]] not to be afraid.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|16:29}}
