{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Orc]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = | AKA = | age = older | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = [[Dol-Makjar]] | family = | partner = | children = | profession = Theater producer | affiliations = [[Halandil Fang]] (business partner) <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x01}} | last = {{ep|4x02}} | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (2 episodes) | television = | comic = | other = }} '''Olgud Akarat''' is an [[orc]]ish theater producer and [[Halandil Fang]]'s business partner. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], Olgud is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Olgud is an older orcish man,{{ep ref|ep=4x01|34:42|name="Intro"}} with dark hair that is graying at the temples.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:36:16}}
=== Personality === Hal's children see Olgud as an uncle,{{ep ref|ep=4x01|36:11}} and at the funeral he is treated as a member of the family; he offers to help receive guests to take some of the burden off Hal.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|36:20}} He is friendly and helpful with [[Tyranny]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:39:35|name="Tyranny"}}
== Biography == === [[Campaign 4]] === Olgud showed up to the farramh of [[Thjazi Fang]], and in conversing with Hal, indicated he was aware of Hal's attempt to get a stay of execution from [[House Halovar]].{{ep ref|ep=4x01|35:27}} He assisted in greeting the guests, and found himself somewhat steamrollered by [[Tyranny]]'s personality when he spoke with her and she convinced him to let her into the kitchen.{{ep ref|ep=4x01|1:36:38}} Once she revealed she was not sure how to behave at a funeral, he offered her advice.<ref name="Tyranny"/> Later, when [[Thaisha]] touched the coffin of [[Olbalad]] and the house shook, Olgud attempted to run interference and prevent guests from going upstairs and interrupting, though he was too intimidated to stop [[Vaelus]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|25:57}}
