{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = Aramán | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Angel]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = | AKA = | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = <!-- Places important or strongly associated to the character history, do not list locations merely because they are seen there incidentally --> | family = | partner = | children = [[Godard Halovar]] | profession = | affiliations = <!-- Major meaningful relationships and group memberships --> <!-- Status --> | status = | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Delete this section if the character is unlikely to ever get stats --> | statsArray1 = {{Infobox Character/stats| | system = d&d | creatureType = [[Celestial]] | background = <!-- Mechanical background, i.e. "Haunted One" --> | alignment = | level = | HP = | AC = | DC = | str = | dex = | con = | int = | wis = | cha = | statsRef = }} <!-- Appearances --> | first = | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (2 episodes) | television = | comic = | other = }} '''Aetheon''' is a feral [[angel]] held captive by [[House Halovar]] beneath [[Villa Aurora]], the source of the [[Candescent Creed]]'s [[Filament]], and the grandfather of [[Wicander Halovar]].
As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Aetheon is a 30 foot tall angel with featherless wings and rows of teeth in his mouth. He is chained within an iron maiden and has taps attached to parts of his body.{{Ep ref|ep=4x02|04:31:14}}
=== Personality === He is feral as a result of the death of [[Tansul]].{{ep ref|ep=4x03|0:28:32}} He is currently screaming as a result of being harvested for [[Filament]] by [[Yanessa Halovar]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02|04:31:55}}
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Aetheon went feral after the death of the [[Shaper]] [[Tansul]]. Afterwards, [[Yanessa Halovar]] acquired him, placing him in an iron maiden underneath [[Villa Aurora]] to extract his blood to create [[Filament]]. Around this time, Yanessa used his blood to make a ''Wish'' for a child, and had [[Godard Halovar]] as a result. Through Godard, the [[House Halovar|Halovar]] bloodline has inherited Aetheon's celestial powers.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|04:29:29}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === Yanessa revealed Aetheon to Wicander, introducing him as Wick's grandfather.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|04:32:30}} She harvests his [[Filament|fluids]] and sells it to the high prince of demons.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|0:42:44}}
