{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = Aramán | actor = Brennan Lee Mulligan | class = [[Sorcerer]] (Shadow Magic) | species = Human <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = | AKA = | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = <!-- Places important or strongly associated to the character history, do not list locations merely because they are seen there incidentally --> | family = [[House Tachonis]] | partner = | children = {{Plainlist| * [[Ethrand Tachonis]] (son) * [[Occtis Tachonis]] (son) }} | profession = | affiliations = <!-- Status --> | status = | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Delete this section if the character is unlikely to ever get stats --> | statsArray1 = {{Infobox Character/stats| | system = d&d | creatureType = | background = <!-- Mechanical background, i.e. "Haunted One" --> | alignment = | level = at least level 18{{ep ref|ep=4x04|name=Umbral Form|more=Primus takes more damage from ''Guiding Bolt'' and can move through creatures and objects, indicating that he was using Umbral Form.}} | HP = | AC = | DC = | str = | dex = | con = | int = | wis = | cha = | statsRef = }} <!-- Appearances --> | first = 4x02 | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (X episodes) | television = <!-- ''[[The Legend of Vox Machina]]'' (X episodes) --> | comic = <!-- Wikilinked comic series title, i.e. the italicized part like "Vox Machina Origins Series II" or "The Tales of Exandria: The Bright Queen" --> | other = <!-- Any works that are not a streamed episode or a comic, including "Pre-stream" and "Kith & Kin" --> }} '''Primus Tachonis''' is the father of [[Occtis Tachonis]] and head of [[House Tachonis]]. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Primus is described as tall and graven, with sallow skin. Shadows lengthen around him, a sign of his sorcerous magic.{{ep ref|ep=4x02}}
== Biography == === [[Campaign 4]] === The day after [[Thjazi Fang]]'s execution, Primus arrived at the [[Penteveral]], interrupting a conversation between [[Ellipides Tallbarrel]] and [[Murray Mag'Nesson]] to tell them that he was looking for his son [[Occtis]].{{ep ref|ep=4x02}} During the conversation with Primus, Murray repeatedly angered him by refusing to be intimidated, to the point that he attempted to curse her and threatened to kill her. Ellipides interceded and Murray left to find [[Azune Nayar]]. Primus told Tallbarrel that he wants her to be fired.{{ep ref|ep=4x03}}
Later that night, Primus and his son [[Ethrand Tachonis|Ethrand]] assaulted [[Palazzo Davinos]], having tracked Occtis there. Primus cast a spell to allow [[shade]]s to cross over from the [[Tenebral Reaches]], and under the cover of his Umbral Form, Primus killed General [[Raimond Davinos]]. Sir [[Julien]] fought back against his father's killer as Primus cast ''Circle of Death'', slaughtering the courtiers inside. He announced his intent to destroy the houses of [[House Royce|Royce]] and [[House Davinos|Davinos]] as Ethrand killed Occtis and implanted the [[Stone of Nightsong]] into his body. Primus then absconded with Ethrand via ''Plane Shift''.{{ep ref|ep=4x04}} <!--Add whatever happened with Occtis's soul that Primus seemingly bore witness to.-->
