=== Personality === Insert character personality here. If there is not a lot of information to dedicate sections for them, consider deleting the header and merging the section upwards.-->
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Lady Zebani Halovar is the daughter of [[Iris Halovar]] and [[Godard Halovar]], who is the son of [[Yanessa Halovar]] that she created through a spell using the "blood" (referred to as [[Filament]]) of the [[celestial]] [[Aetheon]]. To increase [[House Halovar]]'s power, Yanessa devised the [[Candescent Creed]] the obfuscated the origins of Filament. Yanessa needed someone to manage the lower levels of the [[Villa Aurora]], where Aetheon is kept and Filament is drawn out of him, so she informed Zebani of the truth some time before Campaign 4 and tasked with the job.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|0:31:04|name="Basement"}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === Zebani is present when the truth of [[Filament]] and the [[Candescent Creed]] is revealed to Wicander. He is unaware of her presence until after the [[Prismatic Retort]] is opened and he meets Aetheon. She is accompanied by [[Cruelty]]. She grimly tells Wicander that she is glad he knows the truth now like the rest of the family. She stares ahead throughout the following conversation between Yanessa and Wicander about the Creed and Halovar family history. When Wicander asks if he is still the family's scion, Zebani agrees that it is a good question, but Yanessa sharply chides her to not speak. Yanessa describes Zebani as skilled but "not set up to be the face of much of anything"; Wicander defends her as "lovely", but Tyranny scoffs incredulously.<ref name="Basement"/>
== Appearances and mentions == * [[Campaign 4]] ** {{appearance|4x03|appear}}
== Trivia == * ''Zebani'' in Turkish means demon of hell, fiend, hellhound, or a cruel monster<ref>"[https://tureng.com/en/turkish-english/zebani zebani]" at Tureng, a Turkish-English dictionary.</ref> and also refers to the [[WP:Zabaniyah|Zabaniyah]], fallen angels in Islam who torture the wicked in Hell.
