'''General Raimond Davinos''' is the lord of [[House Davinos]] and the father of [[Julien Davinos]]. He and his family serve as a vassal house to the Sundered [[House Royce]]. 

As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], Raimond is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].

== Description ==
{{expand|Add personality}}
Raimond has a silver mustache and goatee. His face is scarred. He wears a golden breastplate and helm. Similar to all of the soldiers of House Davinos, he also wears a gauntlet on his hand.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|2:58:14}}

== Biography ==
=== Before Campaign 4 ===
Raimond fought in the [[War of Axe and Vine]]. Near the end of the war, [[Thjazi Fang]] saved the life of Raimond's nephew, an act that ingratiated Thjazi to Raimond and his house. Because of this friendship, Raimond went against House Royce during the [[Falconer's Rebellion]]. His son Julien rode off against Raimond's orders in order to capture Thjazi and restore their house's status, ending the rebellion.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|3:05:55|3:09:00}}

=== [[Campaign 4]] ===
Raimond arrives at the Tangled Sheet in search of his son, Julien. He scolds Julien for having run off the night after the execution of Lady [[Aranessa Royce|Aranessa's]] estranged husband and demands he get in the carriage. They ride to Palazzo Davinos where Lady Aranessa is waiting for them. There, Raimond informs Julien that [[Occtis Tachonis]] was part of a plot to rescue Thjazi and that [[House Tachonis|his family]] is looking for him. Raimond tasks Julien with intercepting Occtis before the Tachonis find him and bringing him back to the Palazzo so Lady Aranessa may speak with him.{{ep ref|ep=4x02|3:11:03}}

When Julien returns with Occtis, Raimond is there with Aranessa to receive him. He pulls Julien aside and asks if Julien has heard anything about "[[Stone of Nightsong|a stone]]," to which Julien declines and leaves to find Vaelus. A short time later, Raimond follows his son into the gardens, calling out that there was something he wanted to tell Julien, but before he can finish his sentence, Raimond is killed by [[Primus Tachonis]],{{ep ref|ep=4x04|0:31:06}} who spectrally pulled his skull and spine out of his body.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|4:32:42|4:57:28}}

