{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Demon]]{{presumed}} <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him (both) | characterTitles = | AKA = Mercanaud twins | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | languages = [[Demonic]] | place = [[Mercanaud Coturier]], [[Dol-Makjar]] | family = | partner = | children = | profession = Tailor | affiliations = [[House Halovar]] (fixers) <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Delete this section if the character is unlikely to ever get stats -->
<!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x03}} | last = {{ep|4x04}} | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (2 episodes) | television = <!-- ''[[The Legend of Vox Machina]]'' (X episodes) --> | comic = <!-- Wikilinked comic series title, i.e. the italicized part like "Vox Machina Origins Series II" or "The Tales of Exandria: The Bright Queen" --> | other = <!-- Any works that are not a streamed episode or a comic, including "Pre-stream" and "Kith & Kin" --> }} '''Rulius and Calastro Mercanaud''' are the twin proprietors of the [[Mercanaud Coturier]] and work for [[House Halovar]]. As [[non-player character]]s in [[Campaign 4]], they are played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Both twins are older men who wear wigs and ruffs; one wears a platinum wig{{ep ref|ep=4x03|2:57:42}} and the other a gold one.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|2:59:09}} Underneath their wigs, their heads are crystalline and contain flames burning towards the back of the head.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:17:55|name="ToPieces"}} They are scrupulously polite in public, especially to the members of House Halovar and the [[Candescent Creed]].{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:10:14}} They do not have souls.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:13:26}}
== Biography ==
=== [[Campaign 4]] === [[Teor Pridesire]], having been sent to the Mercanaud twins, entered the shop. They greeted him warmly and asked him his purpose, and upon learning he'd been sent by the Candescent Creed, and noticing the white velvet satchel he'd been given, cast ''Hold Person''.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:02:18}} Some time later, [[Wicander Halovar]] and [[Tyranny]] arrived, having decided to save Teor as they knew he'd been sent to the twins to be killed. Rulius answered and was surprised to learn from Tyranny that they wanted Teor before he would be ready in the morning,{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:09:12}} but she convinced him that she and Wick would deal further with Teor instead.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:12:41}} Calastro emerged, clearly having been exerting himself, and retrieved Teor,{{ep ref|ep=4x03|3:15:36}} whose shadow Calastro had been cutting to pieces.{{ep ref|ep=4x03|03:17:55}}
[[Bolaire]] encountered the twins at the [[Speak No Evil]] secret bar in The Fray, where they were inhaling vapor from the ear of a drugged man.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|0:08:19}} He asked them to make a suit like their suits for him, to which they gladly agreed.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|0:09:51}}
