{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = Aramán | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Gnome]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = | AKA = | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = [[Dahapshanee Wood]] | family = | partner = Jasavi (deceased) | children = {{Plainlist| *Cerebel *Demuriel *Elanadel}} | profession = Arcanist, Smuggler | affiliations = <!-- Major meaningful relationships and group memberships --> <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x05}} | last = {{ep|4x05}} | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (1 episode) | television = | comic = | other = }} '''Ulbid Morn''' is a [[gnome|gnomish]] arcanist living in the [[Dahapshanee Wood]]. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Ulbid is an older gnome with white hair, dark skin, a round nose, and a long mustache. He has very large eyebrows.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:02:55}} He studies the clouds of the [[Stormwrack]] from his watchtower,{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:09:36}} and uses the same telescope he uses for his studies to assist smugglers by spying on the roads.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:04:01}}
=== Personality === Ulbid is friendly towards the party, offering them a place to stay and a meal on [[Abalang]]'s word.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:03:47|name="Abalang"}} He is also deeply devoted to his daughters, remaining in his home for many years after he last saw them in the hopes that they will still one day return.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:33:08|name="Welcome"}}
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Ulbid had a wife, Jasavi, who died some time prior to [[Thjazi]]'s execution.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:11:06}} He also has three daughters, Cerebel, Demuriel, and Elanadel, who left to join the [[Falconer's Rebellion]] and did not return.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:32:25}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === After the [[Soldiers' table]] freed Abalang, he told them that if they went through the Dahapshanee Wood, they could seek out Ulbid, who lived in a watchtower within it.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:28:02}} Upon arriving, they noticed a sign in gnomish, which they could not read, and some waterlogged fireworks. They also noticed traps against [[undead]] and [[demon]]s, the latter of which [[Tyranny]] triggered.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:59:23}} Ulbid welcomed them in upon learning they were friends of Abalang.<ref name="Abalang"/> He told them a little about his work, including that the Stormwrack appears to be worsening{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:09:56}} and that he'd seen king's banners on the southward road.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:16:10}} [[Thimble]] found a toy chest in his house, as well as some toy soldiers, and asked him if he could make her [[Thimble's toy sword|a slashing weapon]], to which he agreed.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:19:29}}
While on watch that night, [[Teor]] asked Ulbid about the gnomish banner, and learned that it reads "Welcome Home" for his daughters, who joined the Falconer's Rebellion and never returned. Ulbid told him that he did not know what had happened to them, but could not stand the idea of leaving to search for them and no one being home to greet them. Teor told him that he too was a veteran of the rebellion and would tell his daughters to return should he ever encounter them.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:34:27}}
