{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Mixed ancestry]]: [[half-orc]], half-[[dwarf]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = | AKA = | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = <!-- Places important or strongly associated to the character history, do not list locations merely because they are seen there incidentally --> | family = | partner = | children = | profession = Thief/Smuggler | affiliations = <!-- Major meaningful relationships and group memberships --> <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x05}} | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (1 episode) | television = <!-- ''[[The Legend of Vox Machina]]'' (X episodes) --> | comic = <!-- Wikilinked comic series title, i.e. the italicized part like "Vox Machina Origins Series II" or "The Tales of Exandria: The Bright Queen" --> | other = <!-- Any works that are not a streamed episode or a comic, including "Pre-stream" and "Kith & Kin" --> }} '''Abalang Howl''' is a mixed [[orc]]ish and [[dwarvish]] thief. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], Abalang is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Abalang appears orcish but is very short and stocky, and has a braided beard.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:11:46|name="Intro"}} He is of both orcish and dwarvish heritage.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|0:18:45}}
=== Personality === Abalang is a "fast talker" and considered charming enough to survive in a gibbet by talking people into giving him food.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|3:06:16}} He is forthright with [[Thimble]] and offers his condolences regarding [[Thjazi]]'s death.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:19:01}}
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Thimble and Thjazi had encountered Abalang in [[Dol-Makjar]] a few times prior to Thjazi's execution.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:14:25}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === The [[Soldier's table]] encountered Abalang early in the morning, in a gibbet outside of the Black Heron inn at a crossroads on the way north from Dol-Makjar. He asked them if they could spare some food, which they did, and when Thimble flew up to give it to him, he recognized her and she him.<ref name="Intro"/> He revealed that he had been imprisoned and left to starve or die after stealing from a [[Candescent Creed]] wagon.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:14:51}} [[Wick]], unaccustomed to and opposed to lying, told him that he was a member of [[House Halovar]].{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:16:25}} Thimble meanwhile offered to free Abalang, and was able to do so.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:19:47}} She also asked him if he had seen any [[nama]] on the road from his vantage point, to which he said he had not, but did see a caravan with both [[Crow Keepers]] and [[House Tachonis]] guards.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:23:29}} [[Teor]] healed Abalang, whose legs had gone numb in the gibbet, and [[Tyranny]] convinced him to not reveal who had freed him, but to say that "Nick" had imprisoned him. As the party was leaving their horses to go into the [[Dahapshanee Wood]], they also permitted Abalang to take one.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:24:29}} In thanks, he told them that regardless of the direction they chose, they could use his name to get shelter either at an inn up the road, or at the home of [[Ulbid Morn]], and that he would leave without seeing which direction they chose so that he could honestly say he did not know where they went.{{ep ref|ep=4x05|2:27:24}}
