{{Infobox Character | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = Aramán | actor = Brennan Lee Mulligan | species = <!-- Biographical information --> | pronouns = he/him | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | place = [[Dol-Makjar]], [[Kahad]] | affiliations = [[Crow Keepers]] <!-- Status --> | status = | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> <!-- Delete this section if the character is unlikely to ever get stats --> | statsArray1 = {{Infobox Character/stats| | system = d&d | creatureType = Humanoid }} <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x04}} | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (1 episode) }} '''Aubrus Drime''' is a [[WP:fence (criminal)|fence]] in [[Dol-Makjar]]. He meets with [[Bolaire Lathalia]], a [[panto mask]], and becomes the person wearing Bolaire. As an NPC in [[Campaign 4]] of ''[[Critical Role]]'', Aubrus is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Aubrus is described as an able-bodied man who is "not too terrifically tall" and was of similar proportions to the person Bolaire was previously attached to. He has a shaved head and a nick in one ear.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|0h10m16s|0h17m25s|name="ColdOpen"}}
== Biography == Abrus worked as a typical [[WP:fence (criminal)|fence]] and worked with the [[Crow Keepers]]. By [[Campaign 4]], he established a reputation and sought to work with "a higher class of smuggled goods". He and [[Bolaire Lathalia]] were in communication for some time before arranging a meeting at [[Speak No Evil]] to exchange money and a treasure. He was surprised that Bolaire would work with criminals.<ref name="ColdOpen"/>
At the meeting, he was eager to receive his promised treasure. Angry that Bolaire had nothing, Abrus cast ''Sleep'' on him and removed the mask. Discovering the body was desiccated and withering, he insulted Bolaire as a freak and noted that killing him was unnecessary as he was essentially dead as is.<ref name="ColdOpen"/> He saw a rune on the inside of the mask, which enchanted and charmed him into putting it on. Bolaire then took Abrus over to replace the previous body.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|4h3m28s}}
When Bolaire explained his nature to [[Azune Nayar]], [[Halandil Fang]], and [[Murray Mag'Nesson]], he offered to show them but stated that Aubrus is ornery.{{ep ref|ep=4x04|4h11m33s}}
== Appearances and mentions == * [[Campaign 4]] ** {{appearance|4x04|appear}}
