{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Dryad]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = she/her | characterTitles = | AKA = | age = <!-- Use {{character age}} --> | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = [[Hawthorn's Glade]] | family = | partner = | children = | profession = | affiliations = <!-- Major meaningful relationships and group memberships --> <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Appearances --> | first = | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (1 episode) | television = <!-- ''[[The Legend of Vox Machina]]'' (X episodes) --> | comic = <!-- Wikilinked comic series title, i.e. the italicized part like "Vox Machina Origins Series II" or "The Tales of Exandria: The Bright Queen" --> | other = <!-- Any works that are not a streamed episode or a comic, including "Pre-stream" and "Kith & Kin" --> }} '''Hawthorn''' is a [[dryad]] and the leader of [[Hawthorn's Glade]]. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], she is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Hawthorn moves on a "chariot" of thorns and vines, and has an authoritative voice.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|1:46:30}}
=== Personality === Hawthorn is described as someone who is making difficult and risky choices because she has lost too much by playing it safe.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|2:25:49}}
== Biography == === [[Campaign 4]] === Hawthorn joined a number of other [[fae]] protectors when [[Wick]], [[Tyranny]], [[Thimble]], [[Teor]], and [[Kattigan]] stumbled across the area near her glade. She asked Thimble if she vouched for her mortal companions, and Thimble did so, but what ultimately convinced Hawthorn was Wick's display of power.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|1:53:55}} When she mentioned that another mortal had recently passed through, and Teor and Wick described [[Cyd]], Hawthorn hesitantly invited them to her glade where her tree was.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|2:24:21}} There, she offered them rest and food, and went to speak with [[Soobri]] and [[Sallow]].{{ep ref|ep=4x06|2:36:37}} In that conversation, Thimble learned that Cyd had passed through, and that he had been sent to the [[Wraith Tree]]. Kattigan, having snuck up, joined the conversation, which angered Hawthorn and led her to tell him and Thimble that they had to leave before nightfall.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|2:53:14}} She also told Thimble that she had become too close to mortals and was forgetting her own nature.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|2:57:55}} Sallow later implied that Hawthorn had made the choice to send mortals to the Wraith Tree.{{ep ref|ep=4x06|3:26:14}}
== Appearances and mentions == * [[Campaign 4]] ** {{appearance|4x06|appear|{{1st}}}}
