{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Human]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = she/her | characterTitles = {{Plainlist|* Dame (formerly) * Baroness}} | AKA = | age = {{character age|mid-to-late 30s|c4}} | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = [[Sloak]] | family = | partner = | children = | profession = Knight | affiliations = Order of the Howling Rain <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x08}} | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (1 episode) | television = <!-- ''[[The Legend of Vox Machina]]'' (X episodes) --> | comic = <!-- Wikilinked comic series title, i.e. the italicized part like "Vox Machina Origins Series II" or "The Tales of Exandria: The Bright Queen" --> | other = <!-- Any works that are not a streamed episode or a comic, including "Pre-stream" and "Kith & Kin" --> }} '''Winifred Cosgrove''' is a knight from [[Sloak]]. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], she is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Cosgrove is a broad-shouldered woman in her mid-to-late 30s. She has hair long enough to fall in front of her face, and wears clearly used armor.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
=== Personality === Cosgrove cares deeply about her hometown of Sloak, which is in an impoverished region of [[Gormalay]].{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} She is honorable and is seen by her fellow knights as a leader.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
== Biography == === Before Campaign 4 === Cosgrove grew up in Sloak and fought in the [[Falconer's Rebellion]] on the side of the rebellion in her late teens. Her life was saved by the [[Torn Banner]].{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} Like her father was, she is the sole knight in the Order of the Howling Rain.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
=== [[Campaign 4]] === Cosgrove was among the knights hired by [[Casimir]] upon his assumption of the barony. When [[Kattigan]] used [[Wulferic]] to chase off the horses and mule, Cosgrove went after them.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} She returned after Casimir had been killed, and seemed deeply upset at the idea that the Earl of Gormalay would be choosing a new baron should [[Wick]] turn over the castle to him.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} Wick, at Kattigan and [[Thimble]]'s suggestion, chose to give the title and deed to Cosgrove, who was stunned but grateful.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} When the party and Cosgrove encountered Dame [[Morgaine]] and [[Hawkins]] at the public house, the [[King's Hounds]] approved of this development.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
