{{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = [[Human]] <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = he/him | characterTitles = Sir | AKA = | age = | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = [[Sloak]] | family = | partner = | children = | profession = Knight | affiliations = [[Crow Keepers]] <!-- Status --> | status = Dead | deathReason = drowned in a puddle by [[Hawkins]]{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x07}} | last = {{ep|4x08}} | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (2 episodes) | television = <!-- ''[[The Legend of Vox Machina]]'' (X episodes) --> | comic = <!-- Wikilinked comic series title, i.e. the italicized part like "Vox Machina Origins Series II" or "The Tales of Exandria: The Bright Queen" --> | other = <!-- Any works that are not a streamed episode or a comic, including "Pre-stream" and "Kith & Kin" --> }} '''Sir Gully Breeches''' is a member of the [[Crow Keepers]] who left with [[Casimir Gavendale]] upon Casimir becoming baron of [[Sloak]]. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], he is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Sir Gully Breeches speaks in a cockney accent, and wears a crow cloak,{{ep ref|ep=4x07|3:46:52}} in addition to ill-fitting plate armor.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} [[Teor]] later realized the plate armor was entirely a status symbol and not something he could move in comfortably.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} He is aggressive and defensive of his position,{{ep ref|ep=4x07|3:47:18}} and is disliked by the non-Crow Keeper knights sworn to the Baron of Sloak.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
== Biography ==
=== [[Campaign 4]] === [[Wick]] and [[Tyranny]], using several charm spells, were able to convince Sir Gully Breeches that they were here on behalf of [[House Halovar]] to help tend to Casimir's wounds, and in doing so gain entry into Castle Sloak.{{ep ref|ep=4x07|3:53:00}} Sir Breeches then went with two other knights and several men-at-arms to inform the villagers in Sloak of Casimir's ascension, taking the deed to the castle with him, but as he did so, [[Thimble]] killed Casimir and the rest of their party took the castle.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} They took the deed back from him on his return, at which point Sir Breeches became paranoid and accused this of being a conspiracy.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} The other knights told him he was still sworn to the Baron of Sloak, even if it was no longer Casimir. Gully pretended to agree, then stole one of the horses to flee.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} [[Hawkins]], one of the [[King's Hounds]], caught him and held his head in a puddle until he drowned.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
