{{short description|Hound of the King}} {{Infobox Character <!-- Delete parameters that are unlikely to be ever filled --> | title = <!-- If different from article title --> | image = | caption = <!-- Basic information --> | type = NPC | setting = [[Aramán]] | actor = [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]] | class = | species = Dog{{presumed}} <!-- Biographical information --> | name = <!-- If different from article title --> | pronouns = she/her | characterTitles = Dame | AKA = | age = | languages = <!-- Avoid using if the only entry is "Common" --> | place = [[Timmony]] | family = | partner = | children = | profession = Knight | affiliations = [[Hounds of the King]] <!-- Status --> | status = Alive | deathReason = <!-- Both cause and episode/date go here. Keep this *brief* --> <!-- Mechanical information --> | statsArray1 = {{Infobox Character/stats| | system = d&d | creatureType = [[Beast]] }} <!-- Appearances --> | first = {{ep|4x07}} | last = | stream = [[Campaign 4]] (2 episodes) }} '''Dame Morgaine''' is one of the [[Hounds of the King]]. As a [[non-player character]] in [[Campaign 4]], she is played by [[Brennan Lee Mulligan]].
== Description == Dame Morgaine is a talking dog who is said to look something like a [[W:Bernese mountain dog|Bernese mountain dog]], with brown, white, black, and dark blue splotches.{{ep ref|ep=4x07|2:35:20|name="Mutt"}}
=== Personality === Morgaine is very composed and has an intimidating air,{{ep ref|ep=4x07|2:47:02}} but also has a sense of dry humor and competition with her fellow hound, [[Hawkins]].{{ep ref|ep=4x07|2:52:20}}
== Biography == === [[Campaign 4]] === While traveling to [[Sloak]] to confront [[Casimir Gavendale]] and find [[Cyd Pridesire]], [[Kattigan]] and [[Thimble]] noticed a large mastiff and tracked his steps to a tavern, where they noticed what they believed to be a dog sleeping by the fireplace.<ref name="Mutt"/> In his efforts to gather information, Kattigan began to cast ''Speak with Animals'', but Dame Morgaine interrupted him as she could speak normally.{{ep ref|ep=4x07|2:45:27}} In the ensuing conversation, she told Thimble and Kattigan she was a hound of the king, and when they revealed they were tracking Cyd, she indicated that she would hide their presence from the members of [[House Tachonis]] upstairs.{{ep ref|ep=4x07|2:53:50}} She also told them she would be headed to Sloak the next day as well, and they may encounter her again.{{ep ref|ep=4x07|2:56:17}}
The following day, [[the Soldiers]] encountered her at the public house in Sloak after they had killed Casimir and given the barony to [[Winifred Cosgrove]].{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} Dame Morgaine seemed surprised but also highly pleased by this turn of events,{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}} and she and Hawkins told the group they would head together to [[Tybry's Lea]] to help save Cyd.{{ep ref|ep=4x08|cite=needed}}
